<div id="review_892371975" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/892371975" />
    <a title="Hana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10571559-hana"><img alt="Hana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1458172215p2/10571559.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/892371975?book_show_action=true">Mar 26, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hana" href="/user/show/10571559-hana">Hana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10571559-hana?shelf=adventure-spy">adventure-spy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10571559-hana?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10571559-hana?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10571559-hana?shelf=north-america">north-america</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10571559-hana?shelf=2014-reads">2014-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer892371975" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1139494645028987815">It was wonderful--I had tears in my eyes for most of the last half of the book. Such a hard and beautiful place, the North, with such tough, caring and dignified people.<br/><br/>Kathy&apos;s trip back to Boston was brilliant; that scene where she knocks on a mansion door in Beacon Hill and is refused a glass of water--and then she remembers all the empty trappers cabins up North stocked with wood and provisions and never locked so that any stranger can come in, take shelter and be warm and fed. Kathy matures </span>
  <span id="freeText1139494645028987815" style="display:none">It was wonderful--I had tears in my eyes for most of the last half of the book. Such a hard and beautiful place, the North, with such tough, caring and dignified people.<br /><br />Kathy's trip back to Boston was brilliant; that scene where she knocks on a mansion door in Beacon Hill and is refused a glass of water--and then she remembers all the empty trappers cabins up North stocked with wood and provisions and never locked so that any stranger can come in, take shelter and be warm and fed. Kathy matures so much over the book's seven years and the change in her tone of voice and way of thinking is very well done. <br /><br />I knocked off a star because I thought the first half of the book was uneven in pacing and style and sometimes confusing, but all was forgiven for that powerful, moving and thought-provoking finish.<br /><br />PG warning: extremely painful scenes of death, childbirth, disease (the diphtheria epidemic was particularly horrifying), and all sorts of disasters (amputations without anesthetics, bear maulings, etc). Nothing of the harshness of Northern life was glossed over. On the other hand, only chaste kisses. Nothing even remotely PC about the depiction of Indians, but also plenty of genuine respect.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1139494645028987815" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


