<div id="review_973131465" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/973131465" />
    <a title="MomToKippy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4631503-momtokippy"><img alt="MomToKippy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1412632183p2/4631503.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/973131465?book_show_action=true">Jun 20, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="MomToKippy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="MomToKippy" href="/user/show/4631503-momtokippy">MomToKippy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4631503-momtokippy?shelf=historical-fiction-romance">historical-fiction-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4631503-momtokippy?shelf=travel-fiction">travel-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4631503-momtokippy?shelf=canada">canada</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer973131465" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5369807351080723862">I was going to give this a 3.5 but will leave it at 4 as the ending brought it up for me. This is a fantastic reading experience in terms of understanding the challenges of living in the remote Canadian wilderness at the turn of the century. I really enjoyed learning about the Indians and their culture and their relationships with the &quot;white&quot; settlers/trappers etc. I thought it was portrayed as mostly a positive and respectful one. For this era, the women were exceptionally strong. The story is </span>
  <span id="freeText5369807351080723862" style="display:none">I was going to give this a 3.5 but will leave it at 4 as the ending brought it up for me. This is a fantastic reading experience in terms of understanding the challenges of living in the remote Canadian wilderness at the turn of the century. I really enjoyed learning about the Indians and their culture and their relationships with the "white" settlers/trappers etc. I thought it was portrayed as mostly a positive and respectful one. For this era, the women were exceptionally strong. The story is rife with tragedy which makes it a bit depressing. I found the writing tedious and simplistic at points. However, the last few chapters were absolutely poetic. I wonder if the two authors wrote different portions of the book? I did not know this was based on a true story till I was almost finished and that brings it up for me too. I would love to know Kathy. This book has everything I look for. Historical, foreign adventure, a bit of romance...</span>
  <a data-text-id="5369807351080723862" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


